Pipe break on Shota Rustaveli: traffic changed

05 Nov 2019, 16:08

In Kiev, a number of public transport routes changed traffic due to a pipe break in Shota Rustaveli.
On November 5, a pipe with hot water burst at the intersection of Shota Rustaveli and Saksaganskogo streets in Kiev.
Kievpastrans reports about changes in the routes of trolleybuses and buses due to an accident.

Now traffic is organized as follows:


trolleybuses No. 40 and No. 40K run to the Zheleznodorozhny massif;
trolleybuses No. 3 and No. 9 - to the Yuzhny railway station;
trolleybus number 12 - to the station. metro Lybedskaya;
trolleybus number 14 - to the station. m. Sports Palace;
buses number 69 - to the street Tarasovskaya.

Read: In Kiev, because of the accident, Saksaganskogo street was flooded with boiling water
Recall, due to a breakthrough of the heating system on Shota Rustaveli Street, several cars fell into the pits formed as a result of the accident.
